    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Rather than disallowing it, you might also (in case of a subdirectory) consider to *get all source items first* and than paste it to the destination.\r\nWhat I mean is (sometimes it is easier to explain it in PowerShell than in English ðŸ˜Š):\r\n\r\nInstead of:\r\n<Strike>\r\n```PowerShell\r\nGet-ChildItem A -Recurse |Copy-Item A/A\r\n```\r\n</Strike>\r\n\r\nImplement this (in case it concerns a sub-folder):\r\n```PowerShell\r\n(Get-ChildItem A -Recurse) |Copy-Item A/A # note the parenthesis\r\n```\r\n",
    "created_at": "2022-06-16T07:12:43Z",
